===Etymology===
From {{AGr.}} '''[[ὄν|{{Polytonic|ὄν}}]]''' ([[ōn]]) ‘being’, ‘existing’, ‘essence’ and '''[[λόγος|{{Polytonic|λόγος}}]]''' (logos) ‘account’.  Introduced as a philosophical term by [[w:Christian_Wolff_(philosopher)|Christian Wolf]] (1679-1754).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|ontolog|ies}}

# {{philosophy}} The branch of [[metaphysics]] that addresses the [[nature]] or [[essential]] [[characteristic]]s of [[being]] and of things that [[exist]]; the study of being ''[[qua]]'' being.
# {{philosophy}} The [[theory]] of a [[particular]] philosopher or [[school of thought]] concerning the [[fundamental]] types of [[entity]] in the [[universe]].
#*'''2000''', C.D.C. Reeve, ''Substantial Knowledge: Aristotle's Metaphysics'', Hackett Publishing, p. 97,
